Job Description:
Provide quantitative analysis and attribution for all Clime group investment products;
Maintain and improve Clime Quality Filter;
Responsible for production of data, tables and performance reporting (monthly reports) for all Clime group investment products;
Creation of models to improve the collation, analysis and reporting of investment data;
Identify opportunities to improve efficiency and lower costs of data within the Investment Management team;
Creation of Investment Management Review Committee materials for each fund, portfolio or sub-portfolio;
Support monthly Portfolio Construction and strategy and Investment Management Review meeting materials;
Maintain regular communications cycle, including written and numerical content;
Identify opportunities to improve efficiency within the Investment management team;
Contribute to improved sharing of information within and across teams;
Creation and modification of financial models for required rate of return used in discounted cash flow model, infrastructure sector stock valuation using discounted cash flow model;
As required support Clime Direct, ensuring assigned stocks are kept current at all times, including but not limited to stock valuation updates and stocks out of ‘quarantine’; and
Actively advocate for and display behaviours associated with Clime’s Values.
REQUIRED SKILLS, EXPERIENCE AND QUALIFICATIONS
Advanced Excel modelling capability;
Strong interest in capital markets, fixed income/ credit/ alternative funds management, investor relations, treasury or related investment banking activities (related experience an advantage);
Bachelor’s degree in economics, finance, commerce, mathematics or actuarial studies;
Interest in investment market participants, gatekeepers and opportunities in Australia and Offshore markets;
Sound client relationship management and time management skills;
Effective communication (written and verbal) and interpersonal skills;
Living Clime values, including honesty, integrity, and strong work ethic;
Entrepreneurial spirit: autonomy and responsibility, a ‘can do’ and ‘whatever it takes’ attitude.
